summary: This document is an FBI fingerprint record response from the New York State Division of Criminal Justice Services, indicating that fingerprint data was updated in 2018 and can be accessed through the Interstate Identification Index. It appears to be part of a delayed response to an inquiry.

persons.name: Michael C. Green
persons.role: Executive Deputy Commissioner of the NYS Division of Criminal Justice Services
persons.context: He is listed as the executive deputy commissioner of the agency providing the fingerprint record response.

events.title: Fingerprint record update
events.description: The fingerprint record was updated in the system.

events.title: Delayed response to inquiry
events.description: The FBI and New York State Division of Criminal Justice Services provided a delayed response to an additional inquiry, which included this fingerprint record.

locations: Alfred E. Smith Building, 80 South Swan St. Albany, New York 12210
keyFacts: The document is a fingerprint record response from the New York State Division of Criminal Justice Services to the FBI.
The fingerprint data was last updated on January 16, 2018.
The record can be obtained through the Interstate Identification Index using the appropriate NCIC transaction.
The response is labeled as a 'Delayed Response Additional Inquiry Response' dated October 6, 2021.
